    <h1>Lectures on Rhetoric and Belles Lettres</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Hugh Blair &middot; 1783 &middot; <a href="https://archive.org/details/lecturesonrheto31blaigoog">Full text (Internet Archive, public domain)</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Rhetoric was oral. Blair made it literary. For the first time, someone taught style as a skill you develop through study and practice. "Taste" became learnable, not an aristocratic inheritance.</p>
    </div>

